definitions.definition: ( not in generic modern use ) That which is chief or principal ; the chief or main portion ; the bulk , the greater part , gross .

subdefinitions.definition: ( video games ) The primary character that one plays in a video game in which one can play more than one character.
examples: My WoW main has reached level cap and I’m on my way getting my first alt there as well.
His main got banned after his last post.

definitions.definition: A large cable or pipe providing utility service to an area or a building , such as a water main or electric main . [from 17th c.]
examples: There's a gas leak in the main outside the building.

definitions.definition: ( informal ) Ellipsis of main course ( “ the principal dish of a meal ” ) .
examples: I had scampi and chips for my main and a slice of cheesecake for dessert.

definitions.definition: ( now poetic ) The high seas . [from 16th c.]
( now archaic , US dialectal ) The mainland . [from 16th c.]
( obsolete , except in might and main ) Force , power , strength , violent effort . [from 9th c.]

definitions.definition: ( obsolete , gaming ) A hand or match in a game of dice .
( obsolete , gaming ) The largest throw in a match at dice; in the game of hazard , a number from one to nine called out by a person before the dice are thrown.
( obsolete , gaming ) A stake played for at dice.
( obsolete , gaming , sports ) A sporting contest or match, especially a cockfighting match.
